1
00:00:56,095 --> 00:00:58,973
FILING FOR LOVE

2
00:01:18,450 --> 00:01:19,451
Bye, then.

3
00:01:19,743 --> 00:01:21,161
Would you like some coffee?

4
00:01:21,579 --> 00:01:22,746
No. It's late.

5
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:25,249
Have a cup of cold water, then.

6
00:01:25,332 --> 00:01:26,625
You must be exhausted.

7
00:01:33,507 --> 00:01:34,842
He's pretty hefty.

8
00:01:36,093 --> 00:01:37,469
You're quite strong.

9
00:01:38,971 --> 00:01:40,431
I do what must be done.

10
00:01:40,764 --> 00:01:41,807
Thanks for the water.

11
00:01:47,062 --> 00:01:49,315
Ki-jun and I live together.

12
00:01:51,692 --> 00:01:53,068
It would seem so.

13
00:01:53,152 --> 00:01:54,236
Don't get the wrong idea.

14
00:01:54,320 --> 00:01:57,323
I asked to stay just for a while
due to some personal reasons.

15
00:01:57,406 --> 00:01:58,657
Ki-jun and I are just...

16
00:01:59,366 --> 00:02:00,367
We're just friends.

17
00:02:00,659 --> 00:02:01,660
For now, that is.

18
00:02:02,953 --> 00:02:04,622
We used to date for a bit.

19
00:02:06,749 --> 00:02:07,750
I see.

20
00:02:10,502 --> 00:02:12,838
Thanks. Sorry for the late intrusion.

21
00:02:38,364 --> 00:02:39,531
What are you doing, Joo In-a?

22
00:02:41,075 --> 00:02:42,117
Get a hold of yourself.

23
00:02:48,415 --> 00:02:51,877
EPISODE 6:
CAN'T YOU

24
00:02:53,545 --> 00:02:54,838
Noh Ki-jun, wake up.

25
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:57,257
You can share my taxi
if you get ready in ten minutes.

26
00:02:57,383 --> 00:02:59,301
My headache's killing me.

27
00:03:00,469 --> 00:03:01,804
How did I get home last night?

28
00:03:02,971 --> 00:03:04,014
You just did.

29
00:03:06,058 --> 00:03:07,476
You got back in a pretty state.

30
00:03:08,977 --> 00:03:10,604
My homing instinct never fails.

31
00:03:11,855 --> 00:03:13,857
Good for me. Well done.

32
00:03:18,320 --> 00:03:21,115
I'll get out over there.
You get out at the main entrance.

33
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:22,658
No, it's fine.

34
00:03:23,492 --> 00:03:25,035
Let's just go straight to work.

35
00:03:26,495 --> 00:03:28,664
What's the occasion?
I don't mind this at all.

36
00:03:29,498 --> 00:03:30,582
Okay, then.

37
00:03:40,008 --> 00:03:41,009
Ms. Joo.

38
00:03:41,802 --> 00:03:42,803
Good morning.

39
00:03:44,471 --> 00:03:45,514
Hello.

40
00:03:50,644 --> 00:03:52,187
Did you get home safe last night?

41
00:03:53,689 --> 00:03:56,191
Oh, we had a team dinner.

42
00:03:59,445 --> 00:04:01,739
Yes, I got back just fine,
thanks to you.

43
00:04:02,656 --> 00:04:04,491
- How do you feel...
- Ki-jun?

44
00:04:12,124 --> 00:04:13,208
What's this on you?

45
00:04:13,417 --> 00:04:15,711
You can't look disheveled
in front of your head.

46
00:04:16,920 --> 00:04:18,380
Don't you agree, Ms. Joo?

47
00:04:20,632 --> 00:04:23,010
Well,
I've already seen him disheveled.

48
00:04:31,477 --> 00:04:32,478
What was that about?

49
00:04:40,486 --> 00:04:43,280
What do you think got into her?
Did she eat something weird?

50
00:04:43,781 --> 00:04:45,783
Did you hear about Mr. Do
from Haemu Cosmetics?

51
00:04:46,575 --> 00:04:47,785
Yes.

52
00:04:47,868 --> 00:04:49,828
I'll charge him with assault
and demoralizing behavior

53
00:04:49,912 --> 00:04:51,246
and apply for disciplinary action.

54
00:04:51,330 --> 00:04:52,790
A few of his client companies

55
00:04:52,873 --> 00:04:55,459
severed business ties
due to Mr. Do's actions.

56
00:04:55,542 --> 00:04:56,877
It's a sizable loss.

57
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:58,754
Consult our Legal Team
and consider firing him, too.

58
00:04:59,379 --> 00:05:00,464
I'll do that.

59
00:05:01,632 --> 00:05:03,926
How do you feel, Ms. Joo?

60
00:05:04,426 --> 00:05:05,803
Shouldn't you take a break?

61
00:05:06,678 --> 00:05:09,223
- How about taking the afternoon...
- I'm fine. I'm good.

62
00:05:09,473 --> 00:05:11,266
Could I have become
Haemu's youngest female executive

63
00:05:11,350 --> 00:05:13,894
if I had to take the afternoon
after just a few drinks?

64
00:05:14,478 --> 00:05:15,938
I'm Joo In-a.

65
00:05:16,188 --> 00:05:17,981
Something like that
will never make me...

66
00:05:24,196 --> 00:05:25,489
I will never waver.

67
00:05:27,366 --> 00:05:28,492
Got it.

68
00:05:31,036 --> 00:05:32,037
Respect.

69
00:05:52,891 --> 00:05:55,310
Yes, looking good.

70
00:05:56,353 --> 00:05:57,980
The last frame.

71
00:06:00,983 --> 00:06:02,818
You're doing great, PK.

72
00:06:02,901 --> 00:06:05,153
The photos are amazing.

73
00:06:05,362 --> 00:06:08,031
- What time is it?
- It's a little after 9 p.m.

74
00:06:08,115 --> 00:06:10,534
What? Darn it.

75
00:06:11,535 --> 00:06:13,287
- I'm leaving.
- Where to?

76
00:06:13,620 --> 00:06:15,247
Sort things out for me.
She's waiting.

77
00:06:15,330 --> 00:06:18,166
We still have
a few more outfits to shoot.

78
00:06:18,458 --> 00:06:19,877
PK, where are you going?

79
00:06:43,066 --> 00:06:44,318
What should we do later?

80
00:06:44,401 --> 00:06:45,485
What do you want to do?

81
00:06:46,612 --> 00:06:47,863
Don't get too jumpy.

82
00:06:48,280 --> 00:06:51,325
No, don't. I'm driving right now.

83
00:06:59,833 --> 00:07:01,376
- Hold back.
- What for?

84
00:07:01,460 --> 00:07:03,921
- We have lots of time.
- Kiss me.

85
00:07:04,004 --> 00:07:05,839
- Come on.
- I'm driving.

86
00:07:05,923 --> 00:07:07,299
- We stopped.
- Later.

87
00:07:07,382 --> 00:07:09,217
- No, I want it now.
- Wait.

88
00:07:09,301 --> 00:07:11,720
- Hang on. I really...
- No. Now.

89
00:07:14,848 --> 00:07:16,058
What the heck?

90
00:07:17,559 --> 00:07:18,560
Hey, you!

91
00:07:20,228 --> 00:07:22,856
- Who was that?
- You're dead meat.

92
00:07:28,278 --> 00:07:31,114
Step on it. He's getting away.

93
00:07:31,907 --> 00:07:33,200
He won't stop?

94
00:07:33,492 --> 00:07:35,327
This is so much fun.

95
00:07:45,462 --> 00:07:47,547
Keep going. Catch him.

96
00:07:47,965 --> 00:07:50,384
I want to drive, too.

97
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:51,718
This is fun!

98
00:07:59,059 --> 00:08:00,519
Pull over!

99
00:08:00,852 --> 00:08:02,562
Who are you to take photos?

100
00:08:02,646 --> 00:08:04,231
You! Pull over!

101
00:08:12,906 --> 00:08:15,158
- Darn it.
- Shoot.

102
00:08:15,242 --> 00:08:16,827
We're done for.

103
00:08:17,202 --> 00:08:18,328
What happened?

104
00:08:18,537 --> 00:08:20,372
- Oh, my gosh.
- What the...

105
00:08:21,456 --> 00:08:22,874
I don't believe this.

106
00:08:23,333 --> 00:08:25,002
Are we done for?

107
00:08:25,502 --> 00:08:26,586
Come on out.

108
00:08:26,670 --> 00:08:29,089
- Shoot.
- We're screwed.

109
00:08:30,549 --> 00:08:32,634
Top star singer and actor PK

110
00:08:32,718 --> 00:08:37,055
caused a traffic accident
in a main street late last night.

111
00:08:37,139 --> 00:08:39,224
Reports say it wasn't just a mistake.

112
00:08:39,307 --> 00:08:43,020
He gave chase and drove
into another car deliberately.

113
00:08:43,103 --> 00:08:44,229
Everyone's reeling in shock.

114
00:08:44,312 --> 00:08:45,313
PK, A MIDNIGHT CHASE

115
00:08:45,397 --> 00:08:47,774
Experts say PK
will have to pay a penalty

116
00:08:47,858 --> 00:08:50,652
reaching tens of billions of won
for his commercial deals.

117
00:08:50,736 --> 00:08:53,071
The industry is also in turmoil.

118
00:08:53,155 --> 00:08:54,656
STRIVING FOR THE FUTURE

119
00:08:54,740 --> 00:08:57,117
Come on. PK.

120
00:08:57,868 --> 00:09:00,037
Why did you go and do that?

121
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:02,039
With your handsome face.

122
00:09:06,001 --> 00:09:09,379
- You're a fan of PK?
- Yes, a die-hard fan.

123
00:09:09,713 --> 00:09:13,050
I used to collect PR material for her
if PK was on them.

124
00:09:17,137 --> 00:09:19,473
Does that mean
he's done being our company's model?

125
00:09:23,935 --> 00:09:25,645
- Mr. Moo.
- Yes?

126
00:09:25,729 --> 00:09:27,939
Can I go get a sugar boost?

127
00:09:28,356 --> 00:09:29,941
I have zero will to work right now.

128
00:09:30,025 --> 00:09:32,986
Yes, sure. Get some fresh
and gather yourself.

129
00:09:38,325 --> 00:09:41,620
Why would someone stan
a celebrity at that age?

130
00:09:42,454 --> 00:09:43,705
Don't you agree, Ms. Yoon?

131
00:09:43,789 --> 00:09:45,373
Some people are like that.

132
00:09:45,457 --> 00:09:47,751
Is there a star you like, Ms. Yoon?

133
00:09:47,834 --> 00:09:51,004
Do you think she's the type
to care about celebrities?

134
00:09:51,254 --> 00:09:53,882
She went to a prestigious university
and passed the accountant exam.

135
00:09:53,965 --> 00:09:56,051
- Oh, right.
- She did nothing but study

136
00:09:56,134 --> 00:09:58,428
with no distractions, right?

137
00:09:59,387 --> 00:10:01,681
Look. We're talking about her

138
00:10:01,765 --> 00:10:04,643
and she's concentrating on her work
without minding us.

139
00:10:04,726 --> 00:10:06,770
- She'll be really successful.
- I'm jealous.

140
00:10:16,238 --> 00:10:18,031
NEW MESSAGE
FROM SHIN JI-HYE OF MARKETING

141
00:10:20,534 --> 00:10:22,410
Ki-jun, are you busy?

142
00:10:25,205 --> 00:10:27,666
The wedding invitation looks great.
Congratulations.

143
00:10:28,750 --> 00:10:29,793
Thanks.

144
00:10:31,086 --> 00:10:33,004
Ki-jun, the thing is...

145
00:10:33,839 --> 00:10:35,549
I want to apologize.

146
00:10:37,008 --> 00:10:40,220
For what I did to you
in the stairwell.

147
00:10:40,971 --> 00:10:42,639
I came onto you.

148
00:10:46,017 --> 00:10:48,228
Maybe I have wedding jitters,
like you said.

149
00:10:48,311 --> 00:10:51,189
I've learned my lesson
and turned over a new leaf.

150
00:10:51,565 --> 00:10:53,233
I'll be true and loyal to my husband.

151
00:10:53,316 --> 00:10:55,318
Good. You made the right call.

152
00:10:55,402 --> 00:10:56,528
Live happily ever after.

153
00:10:58,572 --> 00:11:00,031
How are the preparations going?

154
00:11:00,699 --> 00:11:02,576
I'm more worried about my workload.

155
00:11:02,659 --> 00:11:04,161
I hope I'll be done
before the wedding.

156
00:11:04,828 --> 00:11:08,123
Oh, it's because PK messed up, right?

157
00:11:08,832 --> 00:11:11,376
Finding another company model
will be a lot of work.

158
00:11:11,751 --> 00:11:14,504
No, we're not replacing him.

159
00:11:14,588 --> 00:11:16,673
- You're not?
- My team leader put it on hold.

160
00:11:17,215 --> 00:11:19,926
The investigation's still underway,
so she wants to wait.

161
00:11:20,010 --> 00:11:22,596
Why wait?
Isn't a model all about image?

162
00:11:23,054 --> 00:11:24,181
I can't say.

163
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:27,267
PK is still huge abroad.

164
00:11:28,852 --> 00:11:31,771
To be honest, I don't get it, either.

165
00:11:32,439 --> 00:11:33,732
Does PK have connections?

166
00:11:34,608 --> 00:11:35,734
You think so?

167
00:11:44,201 --> 00:11:45,702
Congrats anyway.
See you at the wedding.

168
00:11:45,785 --> 00:11:46,786
Okay.

169
00:11:48,371 --> 00:11:50,665
Ms. Joo,
did you have a meeting elsewhere?

170
00:11:51,333 --> 00:11:53,043
You must have no work to do.

171
00:11:53,126 --> 00:11:56,213
Do you have time to enjoy
a coffee break during work hours?

172
00:11:56,296 --> 00:11:58,715
That's how I gather information.

173
00:11:59,049 --> 00:12:01,134
I think I got something big.

174
00:12:01,218 --> 00:12:03,136
I'm not sure if it's a PM case

175
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:05,347
but my experience tells me
there's more to it.

176
00:12:07,599 --> 00:12:08,600
What is it about?

177
00:12:11,353 --> 00:12:12,479
You know PK, right?

178
00:12:19,986 --> 00:12:22,697
These are all the files
on our company model contracts

179
00:12:22,781 --> 00:12:24,157
going back five years.

180
00:12:27,202 --> 00:12:29,454
Not just signed contracts
but step-by-step reports

181
00:12:29,537 --> 00:12:31,206
minutes, internal memos, invoices

182
00:12:31,289 --> 00:12:34,251
emails that went to and fro
are right here.

183
00:12:34,542 --> 00:12:37,170
Read everything thoroughly
and check for discrepancies.

184
00:12:38,713 --> 00:12:42,801
- I only wanted to look into PK...
- You have a prejudice about him.

185
00:12:42,884 --> 00:12:45,178
That could
make this investigation biased.

186
00:12:46,012 --> 00:12:47,806
And we should compare PK's deal

187
00:12:47,889 --> 00:12:49,975
with that of other models'
to find out if there's a problem.

188
00:12:50,225 --> 00:12:51,268
Right?

189
00:12:51,643 --> 00:12:53,979
Let's get it done ASAP.

190
00:13:07,617 --> 00:13:10,078
How many times must I say I won't go?

191
00:13:10,662 --> 00:13:13,498
Why should I go just to watch
some old folk brag?

192
00:13:13,581 --> 00:13:15,292
I told you about it for a whole month

193
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:17,877
that it's an important event
and you shouldn't drink before going.

194
00:13:19,087 --> 00:13:20,338
So what?

195
00:13:20,714 --> 00:13:22,257
I'm drinking already.

196
00:13:28,054 --> 00:13:29,973
You're an alcoholic.

197
00:13:30,724 --> 00:13:31,766
You need help.

198
00:13:39,024 --> 00:13:40,483
Sorry for laughing.

199
00:13:46,031 --> 00:13:47,198
What?

200
00:13:49,868 --> 00:13:50,952
Are you afraid?

201
00:13:52,287 --> 00:13:54,456
That I'll go crazy like your mom?

202
00:14:01,713 --> 00:14:02,756
Hey.

203
00:14:05,175 --> 00:14:06,968
I told you not to give me that look.

204
00:14:11,598 --> 00:14:13,516
Don't look at me like that!

205
00:14:46,383 --> 00:14:48,301
- Ms. Han.
- Yes?

206
00:14:48,385 --> 00:14:50,095
Are you not picking up
your kids today?

207
00:14:50,178 --> 00:14:53,223
I should leave soon. You go ahead.

208
00:14:55,100 --> 00:14:56,476
Weddings are hard to plan, right?

209
00:14:56,559 --> 00:14:58,436
There's so much to do.

210
00:14:58,520 --> 00:15:00,355
Tell me if you need help
with anything.

211
00:15:00,438 --> 00:15:02,816
- I will. Thank you.
- Go on home.

212
00:15:04,567 --> 00:15:06,986
- See you tomorrow.
- Bye.

213
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,702
What took you so long?

214
00:15:55,785 --> 00:15:58,121
Come here.
You kept me waiting a while.

215
00:16:08,965 --> 00:16:11,009
Why are you going back inside?
Do you have to stay late?

216
00:16:17,307 --> 00:16:18,933
Why do you
keep talking to me at work?

217
00:16:19,017 --> 00:16:20,643
You used to want me to stay away.

218
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:23,021
And why did you fix my tie yesterday

219
00:16:23,104 --> 00:16:24,898
in front of Ms. Joo in the elevator?

220
00:16:24,981 --> 00:16:26,441
You gave me a real scare.

221
00:16:26,524 --> 00:16:29,068
Why are you overreacting?

222
00:16:29,444 --> 00:16:31,738
Is there a reason
Joo In-a can't know?

223
00:16:31,821 --> 00:16:32,822
About us?

224
00:16:33,406 --> 00:16:35,867
No, I'm saying
we should be careful around everyone.

225
00:16:36,451 --> 00:16:37,494
Too bad.

226
00:16:38,495 --> 00:16:40,246
Joo In-a knows already.

227
00:16:42,457 --> 00:16:45,210
That we're living together.

228
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:49,422
- What do you mean?
- Two days ago.

229
00:16:49,506 --> 00:16:52,342
She brought you home
the night you got drunk.

230
00:16:52,425 --> 00:16:53,468
What?

231
00:16:56,638 --> 00:16:58,014
Why are you telling me that now?

232
00:16:58,097 --> 00:17:00,850
I didn't know
it meant so much to you.

233
00:17:04,479 --> 00:17:06,397
Did you tell her
that there's nothing between us?

234
00:17:06,481 --> 00:17:07,857
I told her exactly how things are.

235
00:17:09,067 --> 00:17:10,276
That we used to date.

236
00:17:26,417 --> 00:17:27,585
What's her problem?

237
00:17:53,069 --> 00:17:54,237
Ms. Joo.

238
00:17:54,904 --> 00:17:56,239
Didn't you go home?

239
00:17:56,322 --> 00:17:58,825
I came back
for something I'd forgotten.

240
00:17:59,158 --> 00:18:00,535
Are you finished with this pile?

241
00:18:00,618 --> 00:18:02,328
I don't mind working on it alone.

242
00:18:02,412 --> 00:18:04,539
Let's not waste company funds
on too much overtime.

243
00:18:17,343 --> 00:18:18,595
Did you have dinner?

244
00:18:19,596 --> 00:18:20,597
Would you like to have this?

245
00:18:21,431 --> 00:18:22,432
No.

246
00:18:23,308 --> 00:18:24,309
Okay.

247
00:18:35,987 --> 00:18:39,157
I heard you took me home.

248
00:18:39,741 --> 00:18:42,327
Yes, you should lose some weight.

249
00:18:43,911 --> 00:18:47,290
I weigh more than I look
because I'm pure muscle.

250
00:18:58,968 --> 00:19:01,387
Ms. Park and I are just friends.

251
00:19:01,971 --> 00:19:03,431
We have in separate rooms

252
00:19:03,514 --> 00:19:05,600
and we barely meet at home
because we're both so busy.

253
00:19:05,892 --> 00:19:08,519
Our arrangement
is more like what housemates...

254
00:19:08,603 --> 00:19:09,646
Mr. Noh.

255
00:19:09,729 --> 00:19:11,773
You don't have to explain that to me.

256
00:19:12,899 --> 00:19:14,192
It's your private life.

257
00:19:19,656 --> 00:19:21,449
Don't you care about my private life?

258
00:19:22,533 --> 00:19:23,660
We even kissed.

259
00:19:27,789 --> 00:19:28,956
I don't care.

260
00:19:29,415 --> 00:19:30,750
And don't you care about me.

261
00:19:30,833 --> 00:19:32,543
Didn't we agree to be cool about it?

262
00:19:33,544 --> 00:19:34,921
Then will you

263
00:19:36,047 --> 00:19:37,548
answer my question...

264
00:19:40,051 --> 00:19:41,969
why you push me away.

265
00:19:48,768 --> 00:19:51,312
You asked if I was seeing someone.

266
00:19:52,438 --> 00:19:54,190
Isn't that too personal a question?

267
00:19:54,982 --> 00:19:56,484
We're at work.

268
00:19:56,567 --> 00:19:59,487
Let's stop talking about that
and stick to work-related stuff.

269
00:19:59,570 --> 00:20:01,364
What if it is work-related?

270
00:20:04,659 --> 00:20:05,827
What does that mean?

271
00:20:07,537 --> 00:20:10,206
Can my love life be work-related?

272
00:20:10,289 --> 00:20:11,374
It can.

273
00:20:12,041 --> 00:20:13,960
Depending on who you date.

274
00:20:45,450 --> 00:20:47,076
He didn't come home.

275
00:20:48,161 --> 00:20:50,121
PROPOSAL: COMPANY MODEL

276
00:22:15,957 --> 00:22:18,584
It's definitely suspicious,
even if I look at it without bias.

277
00:22:18,668 --> 00:22:21,629
Haemu first signed PK
as the company model in 2020.

278
00:22:21,712 --> 00:22:23,798
He was unknown then,
and we paid him 300 million won.

279
00:22:26,133 --> 00:22:28,636
When he resigned in 2021,
the pay soared to one billion won.

280
00:22:28,719 --> 00:22:30,054
ONE BILLION KOREAN WON

281
00:22:30,763 --> 00:22:33,558
I don't see why that's a problem.
He soared to stardom in that year.

282
00:22:33,641 --> 00:22:36,018
Almost any model in his caliber
would be paid that much

283
00:22:36,102 --> 00:22:38,145
- and we demanded a lot of him.
- Yes.

284
00:22:38,437 --> 00:22:39,647
You're right about that much.

285
00:22:41,732 --> 00:22:44,318
But then he's criticized
for poor acting

286
00:22:44,402 --> 00:22:47,196
and excessive commercial use
of his image, diminishing his value.

287
00:22:48,197 --> 00:22:50,116
And still, we renew his contract
for five billion won.

288
00:22:50,741 --> 00:22:53,160
And this deal is for three years,
not the customary one year.

289
00:22:53,661 --> 00:22:56,372
I don't think
we were taken advantage of.

290
00:22:56,831 --> 00:22:59,584
It makes me think he has dirt on us.

291
00:23:02,420 --> 00:23:03,754
But guess what the weirdest thing is.

292
00:23:04,338 --> 00:23:06,340
Around the time
we must decide on a model

293
00:23:06,424 --> 00:23:08,968
Marketing communicates immensely
internally and with agencies

294
00:23:09,051 --> 00:23:11,220
to discuss possible models

295
00:23:11,304 --> 00:23:13,598
and to iron out demands
and requirements.

296
00:23:13,681 --> 00:23:14,849
But when it comes to PK

297
00:23:15,725 --> 00:23:16,893
they did nothing of the sort.

298
00:23:17,560 --> 00:23:19,687
They didn't go to his agency once

299
00:23:19,770 --> 00:23:22,231
and they didn't even correspond
via email.

300
00:23:23,274 --> 00:23:25,151
If what should be there is missing

301
00:23:25,234 --> 00:23:28,154
it can mean something
that shouldn't have been there was.

302
00:23:28,654 --> 00:23:29,739
Yes.

303
00:23:31,949 --> 00:23:33,075
The problem is

304
00:23:33,701 --> 00:23:35,786
how do we prove that?

305
00:23:35,870 --> 00:23:37,330
While you were studying the documents

306
00:23:37,413 --> 00:23:40,583
I went through
PK's social media posts.

307
00:23:40,666 --> 00:23:41,667
What?

308
00:23:43,044 --> 00:23:44,253
You had all the fun.

309
00:23:44,837 --> 00:23:46,130
This must've been fun.

310
00:23:46,964 --> 00:23:48,925
It wasn't. My eyes hurt like crazy.

311
00:23:49,425 --> 00:23:50,968
Don't you see how they're bloodshot?

312
00:23:51,052 --> 00:23:52,094
Where?

313
00:24:05,441 --> 00:24:06,692
Anyway.

314
00:24:07,068 --> 00:24:09,695
PK posted something in March 2020.

315
00:24:11,906 --> 00:24:13,032
It's this photo.

316
00:24:13,282 --> 00:24:15,034
It looked expensively luxurious

317
00:24:15,451 --> 00:24:17,787
so I zoomed in on this window
and looked it up.

318
00:24:18,371 --> 00:24:22,500
It's a crazy expensive
private hot spring in Osaka, Japan.

319
00:24:23,125 --> 00:24:25,795
He's a celebrity, so he would
go on a date at a place like this.

320
00:24:26,295 --> 00:24:27,380
Right.

321
00:24:29,382 --> 00:24:31,133
At around this time

322
00:24:31,384 --> 00:24:33,511
this exact same period

323
00:24:34,220 --> 00:24:36,555
there's a Haemu employee
who used their company card in Osaka.

324
00:24:37,682 --> 00:24:39,433
The transaction
was canceled right away

325
00:24:39,517 --> 00:24:42,895
but I can't say if it was because
she felt a pang of guilt

326
00:24:42,979 --> 00:24:44,814
or because she wanted
to erase her trace.

327
00:24:46,816 --> 00:24:51,195
But Osaka is one of the places
where Koreans love to visit.

328
00:24:51,946 --> 00:24:54,281
It could just be a coincidence.

329
00:24:55,992 --> 00:24:57,368
What if that employee

330
00:25:00,162 --> 00:25:01,706
had the final say in signing PK?

331
00:25:03,165 --> 00:25:04,500
Doesn't that change everything?

332
00:25:08,254 --> 00:25:10,381
TEAM LEADER HAN JI-WON

333
00:25:21,308 --> 00:25:22,601
Are you a slow reader?

334
00:25:23,185 --> 00:25:24,895
You're taking way too long.

335
00:25:26,939 --> 00:25:28,524
COMPANY MODEL: PK
STANDARD CONTRACT

336
00:25:28,941 --> 00:25:30,860
It's okay. Take your time.

337
00:25:31,527 --> 00:25:32,695
Thank you.

338
00:25:40,411 --> 00:25:43,414
We follow the due process
when selecting a company model.

339
00:25:44,248 --> 00:25:46,083
But in PK's case

340
00:25:46,167 --> 00:25:48,252
we've had a long-standing
model-client relationship

341
00:25:48,335 --> 00:25:50,171
and I guess that's why
things were a bit lax.

342
00:25:50,629 --> 00:25:51,630
What about the Japan trip?

343
00:25:52,465 --> 00:25:53,924
That was pure coincidence.

344
00:25:54,592 --> 00:25:57,678
I went there on a family trip
with my two kids and husband.

345
00:25:58,596 --> 00:25:59,930
I used the wrong credit card.

346
00:26:00,514 --> 00:26:04,226
I used it at a convenience store,
but I canceled it right away.

347
00:26:05,811 --> 00:26:07,396
You went with your family.

348
00:26:08,105 --> 00:26:10,149
Can I see the photos you took?

349
00:26:11,484 --> 00:26:14,987
I'd love to show you,
but I got a new phone recently.

350
00:26:15,237 --> 00:26:16,822
I don't have any of the photos.

351
00:26:16,906 --> 00:26:17,990
?Oh, dear.

352
00:26:18,074 --> 00:26:20,034
You lost all the photos of your kids?

353
00:26:20,367 --> 00:26:21,619
You didn't save them
to a cloud server?

354
00:26:22,870 --> 00:26:25,164
I didn't. I'm not that good
with technology.

355
00:26:25,748 --> 00:26:27,291
Let's see your phone.

356
00:26:27,625 --> 00:26:29,126
- What?
- I don't believe you.

357
00:26:29,210 --> 00:26:30,669
Let me see your phone.

358
00:26:31,587 --> 00:26:34,799
Do I have to show you my phone?

359
00:26:34,882 --> 00:26:36,342
It's our due process.

360
00:26:37,009 --> 00:26:39,095
You'll sign a consent form
before handing it over.

361
00:26:39,553 --> 00:26:42,348
Of course,
you can refuse to turn it in.

362
00:26:43,182 --> 00:26:45,893
But that won't do you any good.

363
00:26:49,188 --> 00:26:51,023
It wasn't a family trip.

364
00:26:51,315 --> 00:26:54,527
What Korean mom
takes her kids to a hot spring

365
00:26:54,610 --> 00:26:57,905
in Japan in March, the month
her first kid starts school?

366
00:26:58,239 --> 00:27:00,241
We know your husband didn't travel.

367
00:27:00,866 --> 00:27:02,243
We confirmed it already.

368
00:27:19,218 --> 00:27:20,344
We're dating.

369
00:27:22,930 --> 00:27:24,056
PK and I.

370
00:27:26,809 --> 00:27:28,018
We're lovers.

371
00:27:38,863 --> 00:27:40,990
Ms. Han gave in too easily.

372
00:27:41,824 --> 00:27:43,909
I interviewed her coworkers
beforehand

373
00:27:44,493 --> 00:27:46,328
and they said
she was stubborn and uptight.

374
00:27:47,037 --> 00:27:49,123
I even prepared a few more scenarios
to use against her.

375
00:27:51,041 --> 00:27:52,042
Are you busy today?

376
00:28:08,017 --> 00:28:09,101
Oh, dear.

377
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:28,787
Min-yul, sit up straight
and wear your seat belt.

378
00:28:28,871 --> 00:28:29,997
It's my turn now.

379
00:28:31,332 --> 00:28:32,875
- I got it.
- You're done for the day?

380
00:28:32,958 --> 00:28:35,377
Come on. Give it back to me.

381
00:28:35,461 --> 00:28:37,546
You won't even say hi to Mom.

382
00:28:39,798 --> 00:28:41,467
Don't run, boys.

383
00:28:43,219 --> 00:28:44,553
Dong-yun, turn that off.

384
00:28:45,054 --> 00:28:47,389
Honey, I'm so very sorry.

385
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:50,309
I barely shut down my boss
who wanted to go for round two.

386
00:28:50,392 --> 00:28:52,728
- Good for you.
- Dong-yun, you won't even say hi?

387
00:28:55,481 --> 00:28:57,149
Don't you love dumplings?

388
00:28:57,524 --> 00:28:59,652
Can we have some? Try one.

389
00:28:59,735 --> 00:29:01,403
- Leave it.
- Come on.

390
00:29:01,487 --> 00:29:02,988
- Don't be silly.
- Open wide.

391
00:29:05,574 --> 00:29:07,868
They seem to be happily married.

392
00:29:07,952 --> 00:29:09,203
Yes.

393
00:29:09,286 --> 00:29:11,747
- Isn't she too busy to have a lover?
- We'll take a pack.

394
00:29:12,790 --> 00:29:14,583
Thank you. Bye.

395
00:29:16,669 --> 00:29:19,004
Lee Dong-yun.
Quit playing on that phone.

396
00:29:21,757 --> 00:29:23,759
Yes, that one, maybe.

397
00:29:37,022 --> 00:29:38,941
Is Ms. Han really PK's lover?

398
00:29:39,024 --> 00:29:40,442
Is that why she favored him?

399
00:29:40,526 --> 00:29:42,695
Is this the sponsor thing
I'd only heard about?

400
00:29:42,778 --> 00:29:44,822
Where would she get the money for it?

401
00:29:44,905 --> 00:29:47,366
Does she make much more than I
when I'm also a team leader?

402
00:29:47,449 --> 00:29:48,909
- No.
- He said

403
00:29:48,993 --> 00:29:51,453
he was too busy with work to date

404
00:29:51,537 --> 00:29:54,623
and he acted all sweet and naive,
like he only cared for his fans.

405
00:29:55,332 --> 00:29:58,335
I didn't believe every word he said

406
00:29:58,419 --> 00:30:00,129
but isn't this just wrong?

407
00:30:00,462 --> 00:30:04,341
How could he sleep around
with a married mom of three?

408
00:30:04,883 --> 00:30:07,511
The second-hand embarrassment
is killing me.

409
00:30:14,768 --> 00:30:16,395
- What's wrong?
- What are you doing?

410
00:30:17,354 --> 00:30:19,273
Why are you suddenly
cleaning out your drawer?

411
00:30:21,191 --> 00:30:22,609
- What...
- Why...

412
00:30:23,861 --> 00:30:25,070
What's wrong?

413
00:30:25,696 --> 00:30:27,781
- Why the sudden outburst?
- This is...

414
00:30:30,200 --> 00:30:31,535
It's PK's merchandise.

415
00:30:33,037 --> 00:30:35,456
No one can confirm who was in his car

416
00:30:35,748 --> 00:30:38,250
at the time of the accident?

417
00:30:39,043 --> 00:30:41,003
That's right.
No one has any information.

418
00:30:41,086 --> 00:30:42,713
Even the reporters
are getting frustrated.

419
00:30:43,630 --> 00:30:46,300
If Ms. Han is telling a lie...

420
00:30:47,426 --> 00:30:49,887
Why on earth? It would get her fired.

421
00:30:50,971 --> 00:30:53,682
Could there be something
she fears more than losing her job?

422
00:31:00,314 --> 00:31:02,399
I told you
not to over-water the plant.

423
00:31:04,860 --> 00:31:06,612
You told me?

424
00:31:08,072 --> 00:31:09,490
I'm your superior.

425
00:31:13,243 --> 00:31:15,245
It's better to be straightforward.

426
00:31:17,247 --> 00:31:18,374
Put that down.

427
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:25,798
It doesn't feel right

428
00:31:26,632 --> 00:31:28,717
that Ms. Han is PK's lover.

429
00:31:29,093 --> 00:31:30,844
The women PK dated so far

430
00:31:30,928 --> 00:31:32,930
are idol singer Ha Jeong-yun,
actress Yang Hee-seung

431
00:31:33,013 --> 00:31:35,265
hotel heiress Jo Moon-joo,
and influencer Lee Ji-hyun.

432
00:31:35,349 --> 00:31:37,059
They're all puppy-faced girls

433
00:31:37,142 --> 00:31:39,686
who are relatively short and cute.

434
00:31:39,770 --> 00:31:42,356
But Ms. Han's awfully tall

435
00:31:42,439 --> 00:31:43,899
and she has cat-like features.

436
00:31:44,775 --> 00:31:45,984
Not to mention she's married.

437
00:31:47,069 --> 00:31:48,695
She's not even rich enough
to be a sponsor.

438
00:31:49,363 --> 00:31:51,448
Gosh, Ms. Yoon.

439
00:31:52,199 --> 00:31:54,493
You seem to know a great deal
about PK.

440
00:31:56,870 --> 00:31:58,038
I used to be a fan.

441
00:31:59,248 --> 00:32:00,582
I quit just now.

442
00:32:02,835 --> 00:32:05,045
You must've been a die-hard fan.

443
00:32:06,422 --> 00:32:07,423
Do you know

444
00:32:08,507 --> 00:32:09,800
where to look?

445
00:32:10,384 --> 00:32:12,845
How about rumors among real fans?

446
00:32:13,720 --> 00:32:14,721
Or how about

447
00:32:15,305 --> 00:32:17,099
social media posts about PK?

448
00:32:22,563 --> 00:32:24,898
There's a well-known PK stalker fan

449
00:32:25,482 --> 00:32:27,067
that all the other fans know about.

450
00:32:28,485 --> 00:32:31,405
He said he had photos
from the scene of the accident.

451
00:32:31,697 --> 00:32:33,866
He made a threatening post.

452
00:32:33,949 --> 00:32:35,826
WE'LL PROTECT YOU, PK
STAY STRONG, PK

453
00:32:36,660 --> 00:32:38,579
He might know something.

454
00:32:41,707 --> 00:32:42,958
STAY STRONG, PK
WE'RE BY YOUR SIDE

455
00:32:54,553 --> 00:32:56,513
Are you PK Rabbit?

456
00:32:56,597 --> 00:32:58,390
I recognized your rabbit ears.

457
00:32:58,474 --> 00:32:59,725
They're adorable.

458
00:33:02,144 --> 00:33:03,145
Yikes.

459
00:33:09,693 --> 00:33:12,404
I'm the person who sent you the DM.

460
00:33:13,947 --> 00:33:15,574
I wanted to buy a photo card.

461
00:33:16,074 --> 00:33:17,701
Are you really here for a photo card?

462
00:33:18,702 --> 00:33:20,996
Aren't you from some large company?

463
00:33:22,789 --> 00:33:24,750
I am from a large company,
but how do you know...

464
00:33:27,419 --> 00:33:29,171
Why? What do you want?

465
00:33:30,339 --> 00:33:32,966
What's the matter? What's this about?

466
00:33:43,310 --> 00:33:46,021
The photos I gave you last time
were all I had.

467
00:33:46,605 --> 00:33:48,106
I didn't make any copies.

468
00:33:48,649 --> 00:33:50,484
- And please, mister.
- Yes, what?

469
00:33:50,567 --> 00:33:51,735
I'll quit being a fan.

470
00:33:51,818 --> 00:33:54,112
I won't take any more photos

471
00:33:54,196 --> 00:33:55,906
and I won't follow PK around anymore.

472
00:33:56,323 --> 00:34:00,744
- What's this about? Get up.
- So please, leave me alone.

473
00:34:01,453 --> 00:34:05,415
- I'm not...
- Your company is bullying people!

474
00:34:19,471 --> 00:34:21,640
What company are you talking about?

475
00:34:24,977 --> 00:34:29,856
Aren't you from Sesan Group?

476
00:34:31,567 --> 00:34:32,776
Sesan Group?

477
00:34:35,320 --> 00:34:36,863
These are the originals.

478
00:34:37,281 --> 00:34:38,949
I confirmed there are no copies.

479
00:34:47,499 --> 00:34:48,625
Good job.

480
00:34:50,669 --> 00:34:51,753
Nice one.

481
00:34:57,634 --> 00:35:02,055
Did you really say
you and I were dating?

482
00:35:04,141 --> 00:35:06,018
Did they believe that?

483
00:35:07,144 --> 00:35:08,520
What idiots.

484
00:35:11,273 --> 00:35:13,275
I'll post your husband to Europe.

485
00:35:14,026 --> 00:35:15,235
Flee quietly.

486
00:35:37,549 --> 00:35:39,760
As people say, former fans
can be the scariest haters.

487
00:35:42,596 --> 00:35:43,847
Anyway.

488
00:35:44,222 --> 00:35:46,391
I've been a PK stan for years
while you worked with me.

489
00:35:46,475 --> 00:35:48,352
How come
you never even brought it up?

490
00:35:49,353 --> 00:35:50,354
Gosh.

491
00:35:52,064 --> 00:35:53,106
Ms. Yoon.

492
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:56,443
I know you aren't looking
to make friends at work

493
00:35:57,361 --> 00:35:58,945
but this one was too harsh.

494
00:36:08,580 --> 00:36:10,248
Isn't this
the exclusive fan club merch?

495
00:36:11,041 --> 00:36:12,417
And it's the first generation.

496
00:36:13,752 --> 00:36:17,172
The resale price for this is crazy.
Why did you throw it out?

497
00:36:17,255 --> 00:36:18,298
That benefits no one.

498
00:36:18,382 --> 00:36:20,634
At least sell it and eat
some tteokbokki with the money.

499
00:36:25,305 --> 00:36:26,348
Well.

500
00:36:26,765 --> 00:36:28,600
I can treat you today.

501
00:36:29,643 --> 00:36:31,061
I sold a few things already.

502
00:36:32,062 --> 00:36:33,313
I'm rich now.

503
00:36:42,656 --> 00:36:43,949
I can never say

504
00:36:46,243 --> 00:36:47,327
no to tteokbokki.

505
00:36:49,830 --> 00:36:50,831
Let's go.

506
00:36:52,708 --> 00:36:54,292
Wait up, Ms. Yoon.

507
00:36:55,085 --> 00:36:57,629
How do you like your tteokbokki?
Made with flour or rice?

508
00:36:57,713 --> 00:36:58,755
I'm a rice girl.

509
00:37:00,215 --> 00:37:02,384
What is it? Tell me.

510
00:37:02,676 --> 00:37:04,928
It seems like you and I have
the same taste in things.

511
00:37:06,054 --> 00:37:08,056
I told you
to carry the ball with you.

512
00:37:08,140 --> 00:37:09,349
You're going to hurt people.

513
00:37:10,016 --> 00:37:11,810
Min-yul! Goodness.

514
00:37:18,900 --> 00:37:19,985
So?

515
00:37:21,111 --> 00:37:22,112
Are you any good at soccer?

516
00:37:25,073 --> 00:37:26,199
Hey.

517
00:37:26,324 --> 00:37:27,826
Go out! And shoot!

518
00:37:27,909 --> 00:37:29,286
Hey, wait!

519
00:37:29,703 --> 00:37:31,496
- Start running.
- Wait for me!

520
00:37:31,580 --> 00:37:32,831
Get the ball!

521
00:37:33,498 --> 00:37:35,792
- Here!
- What are you doing?

522
00:37:35,876 --> 00:37:37,544
What are you doing, man?

523
00:37:41,339 --> 00:37:44,176
Hey, this is cheating!

524
00:37:44,259 --> 00:37:45,635
Stop! I said, stop!

525
00:37:46,845 --> 00:37:48,221
Stand in a line right here.

526
00:37:48,638 --> 00:37:51,308
You aren't supposed
to play dirty, boys.

527
00:37:51,391 --> 00:37:52,517
Play fair.

528
00:37:53,310 --> 00:37:54,519
Isn't that right, Mommy?

529
00:37:58,064 --> 00:38:00,275
Now, go out and play!

530
00:38:01,443 --> 00:38:03,904
- I got it.
- Hey, you can't play alone!

531
00:38:03,987 --> 00:38:05,155
- Wait!
- I'm so tired.

532
00:38:14,039 --> 00:38:16,583
You raise three boys and yet,
you're the Marketing Team Lead.

533
00:38:16,833 --> 00:38:18,418
You're something, Ms. Han.

534
00:38:22,005 --> 00:38:23,465
Plus, you have a guy on the side.

535
00:38:25,091 --> 00:38:26,301
Aren't you going on a date today?

536
00:38:30,180 --> 00:38:32,557
Your husband works
for Sesan Group, doesn't he?

537
00:38:35,227 --> 00:38:37,354
That must've become your weakness.

538
00:38:37,604 --> 00:38:38,939
She doesn't have any power over us

539
00:38:39,523 --> 00:38:41,817
but her influence
can't be ignored at Sesan.

540
00:38:52,410 --> 00:38:54,204
It looks like
you already know everything.

541
00:38:55,497 --> 00:38:56,832
What's your plan now?

542
00:38:58,166 --> 00:38:59,209
What did she say?

543
00:38:59,292 --> 00:39:00,627
We were told to move abroad.

544
00:39:01,169 --> 00:39:02,963
She'll post my husband overseas.

545
00:39:04,130 --> 00:39:05,423
Once I disappear

546
00:39:06,299 --> 00:39:08,677
the case will dissolve because
the person responsible isn't around

547
00:39:09,177 --> 00:39:10,887
and PK will continue to model for us.

548
00:39:12,889 --> 00:39:14,724
Those two will
continue to have an affair

549
00:39:14,808 --> 00:39:16,059
while only you're known as a woman

550
00:39:17,102 --> 00:39:18,520
who slept with a celebrity,
gave him a gig

551
00:39:18,603 --> 00:39:20,522
and then fled abroad
once you got caught?

552
00:39:22,440 --> 00:39:24,568
You're going to be a legend.

553
00:39:26,653 --> 00:39:29,489
So 15 years of diligent service
since the day you began at age 25

554
00:39:30,198 --> 00:39:31,241
comes to nothing?

555
00:39:33,118 --> 00:39:35,912
Well, that kind of rumor
is probably not the worst.

556
00:39:37,247 --> 00:39:39,374
I told your sons
that I was your friend from work.

557
00:39:39,958 --> 00:39:41,710
That kid is Min-uk,
your second son, right?

558
00:39:42,002 --> 00:39:43,295
He asked me

559
00:39:44,004 --> 00:39:45,380
if I were the captain's friend.

560
00:39:45,797 --> 00:39:47,799
He said his mother
was the captain at work

561
00:39:49,301 --> 00:39:52,345
so I should listen to you
and never cause any trouble.

562
00:39:53,471 --> 00:39:56,182
What a caring son you have.
He should be more obedient.

563
00:39:56,266 --> 00:39:57,267
Don't you think?

564
00:39:58,310 --> 00:40:00,687
I told him that I was a team leader,
not a captain.

565
00:40:06,610 --> 00:40:07,652
Do you want help?

566
00:40:12,866 --> 00:40:15,493
I'm a pretty useful shield, actually.

567
00:40:17,579 --> 00:40:18,705
Don't you want to use me?

568
00:40:19,497 --> 00:40:22,083
I promised the boys
that I'd keep the captain safe.

569
00:40:36,222 --> 00:40:37,349
All right.

570
00:40:37,432 --> 00:40:39,601
I'm good now. I've resurrected.

571
00:40:40,310 --> 00:40:42,312
- Come at me again.
- Okay!

572
00:41:02,499 --> 00:41:04,876
- Wait! It's my ball!
- No, it's mine!

573
00:41:04,960 --> 00:41:06,628
Pass it behind you.

574
00:41:06,711 --> 00:41:08,964
Over here! Pass it to me.

575
00:41:11,633 --> 00:41:14,344
Thus, the fundamental issue here is

576
00:41:14,427 --> 00:41:17,806
that Ms. A could pressure Marketing
into showing favor to the model Mr. B

577
00:41:17,889 --> 00:41:20,225
because of the system we created
for advertisement production.

578
00:41:21,851 --> 00:41:24,646
Hence, we propose a measure
to reinforce transparency in the...

579
00:41:24,729 --> 00:41:26,064
Hey, wait a second.

580
00:41:27,691 --> 00:41:28,817
I mean, please.

581
00:41:29,234 --> 00:41:30,485
Who's Ms. A?

582
00:41:30,568 --> 00:41:32,529
I get that Mr. B, the model, is PK.

583
00:41:32,612 --> 00:41:35,532
You have to tell us who Ms. A is.
We're dying to know who it is.

584
00:41:35,615 --> 00:41:37,242
That's not the point of the issue.

585
00:41:37,325 --> 00:41:39,452
Bringing up the actual name
may be considered libel.

586
00:41:39,536 --> 00:41:42,205
Come on. We aren't strangers here.

587
00:41:42,288 --> 00:41:44,165
Libel? Don't make me sad.

588
00:41:44,249 --> 00:41:46,960
We apologize that we could not share
every aspect of the case.

589
00:41:47,627 --> 00:41:49,713
However,
once Ms. A's identity is disclosed

590
00:41:50,005 --> 00:41:52,674
it may create a bigger business risk.

591
00:41:53,049 --> 00:41:54,718
I appreciate your understanding.

592
00:41:54,884 --> 00:41:58,930
Who in the world is it?

593
00:42:02,851 --> 00:42:03,893
Hyun-young.

594
00:42:04,436 --> 00:42:05,937
What brings you here?

595
00:42:13,611 --> 00:42:14,988
Who's Joo In-a?

596
00:42:34,215 --> 00:42:36,092
Who do you think you are to fire PK?

597
00:42:36,426 --> 00:42:38,178
Who do you think you are, you wench?

598
00:42:38,261 --> 00:42:41,473
How dare you fire him?
Who do you think you are?

599
00:42:46,686 --> 00:42:48,855
What are you doing? Let go.

600
00:42:49,898 --> 00:42:51,024
Let go!

601
00:42:51,649 --> 00:42:52,859
I said, let go!

602
00:43:04,579 --> 00:43:07,499
Hey, Jeon Jae-yeol.
Have you lost your mind?

603
00:43:07,582 --> 00:43:09,501
Have you? Answer me!

604
00:43:12,295 --> 00:43:13,963
Who do you think you are to fire PK?

605
00:43:14,047 --> 00:43:15,548
How dare you mess with him?

606
00:43:16,424 --> 00:43:17,550
Didn't you hear me?

607
00:43:18,051 --> 00:43:19,969
Hey, answer me.

608
00:43:21,387 --> 00:43:22,680
Answer me!

609
00:43:37,695 --> 00:43:39,030
Do you think I'm a joke?

610
00:43:39,531 --> 00:43:41,449
It's not even a big deal,
but you blew it up.

611
00:43:42,826 --> 00:43:45,161
Wait, are you jealous? Are you?

612
00:43:45,954 --> 00:43:49,707
Have I ever said anything
about your infidelity?

613
00:43:50,834 --> 00:43:53,336
At the very least, it shouldn't have
impacted my business.

614
00:43:53,419 --> 00:43:55,672
I didn't do anything.
I didn't even take money from him.

615
00:43:55,755 --> 00:43:57,674
All of you are way disgusting,
so you don't get to do this.

616
00:43:59,634 --> 00:44:02,137
Can you say what you just said
in front of your father?

617
00:44:02,220 --> 00:44:04,931
I'll kill myself
if you dare to do that.

618
00:44:05,557 --> 00:44:06,599
Go ahead.

619
00:44:07,642 --> 00:44:08,852
Go ahead and do that if you can.

620
00:44:11,729 --> 00:44:12,939
This time

621
00:44:13,940 --> 00:44:15,275
you crossed the line for good.

622
00:44:17,902 --> 00:44:19,362
Leave the country immediately.

623
00:44:19,863 --> 00:44:21,364
Don't dream of returning for a while.

624
00:44:23,366 --> 00:44:25,743
Hey!

625
00:44:48,308 --> 00:44:50,268
Why does this always happen
to the Head of Audit?

626
00:44:50,351 --> 00:44:52,604
You're always getting beaten up, hurt

627
00:44:53,271 --> 00:44:54,355
and criticized.

628
00:44:55,398 --> 00:44:56,399
That really hurts.

629
00:44:56,941 --> 00:44:58,735
Be more gentle
and leave your feelings out of it.

630
00:45:01,821 --> 00:45:03,948
Now, stay still.

631
00:45:09,454 --> 00:45:10,538
All done.

632
00:45:13,750 --> 00:45:15,084
Gosh, it hurts.

633
00:45:15,877 --> 00:45:17,086
Don't be a drama queen.

634
00:45:19,672 --> 00:45:21,257
What happened to your legs?

635
00:45:21,341 --> 00:45:23,551
One of them is bruised,
and the other is scraped.

636
00:45:23,635 --> 00:45:26,888
These? I got tackled
by Son Heung-min of Mapo-dong.

637
00:45:27,513 --> 00:45:29,057
Wait, you play soccer?

638
00:45:29,974 --> 00:45:32,101
Gosh, you have so many hobbies.

639
00:45:33,937 --> 00:45:35,605
Did you disinfect your legs?

640
00:45:35,688 --> 00:45:38,024
I'm fine. Leave them.
They'll get better soon.

641
00:45:41,569 --> 00:45:42,862
Stay still.

642
00:45:51,454 --> 00:45:53,873
Models aren't supposed to have
any wounds on their bodies.

643
00:45:54,666 --> 00:45:56,000
Where's your work ethic?

644
00:46:25,530 --> 00:46:27,782
About your question, Mr. Noh...

645
00:46:31,703 --> 00:46:33,830
The real reason
why I keep pushing you away...

646
00:46:41,129 --> 00:46:42,130
I...

647
00:46:50,346 --> 00:46:51,472
I...

648
00:46:57,145 --> 00:46:58,646
It's due next week.

649
00:46:59,772 --> 00:47:00,940
Next week?

650
00:47:03,818 --> 00:47:04,861
Mr. Noh.

651
00:47:05,111 --> 00:47:08,072
The one who just left
was Joo In-a, right?

652
00:47:08,990 --> 00:47:10,950
Gosh, were you getting scolded again?

653
00:47:11,034 --> 00:47:12,327
No, you should get to work.

654
00:47:17,582 --> 00:47:18,708
Ms. Joo.

655
00:47:23,129 --> 00:47:24,464
Let me apologize on her behalf.

656
00:47:24,547 --> 00:47:25,673
It's okay.

657
00:47:37,185 --> 00:47:38,227
Hey.

658
00:47:44,233 --> 00:47:45,276
NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT

659
00:47:45,360 --> 00:47:48,196
It's an NDA that says
you will not say anything

660
00:47:48,279 --> 00:47:49,697
about what you've seen today.

661
00:47:49,781 --> 00:47:53,117
But why? Do you think I'll go out
and tell the whole world

662
00:47:53,201 --> 00:47:54,869
that our vice president's wife
is a crazy psycho?

663
00:47:54,952 --> 00:47:56,621
We're just making sure.

664
00:47:56,788 --> 00:47:59,582
Everyone who was there
had to sign this

665
00:47:59,665 --> 00:48:01,042
so don't overthink it.

666
00:48:01,584 --> 00:48:03,086
You can sign it down there.

667
00:48:08,299 --> 00:48:10,259
You didn't expect that
from the vice president, did you?

668
00:48:12,178 --> 00:48:14,889
He looks perfect and sleek
from the outside.

669
00:48:16,099 --> 00:48:18,017
But once you unravel him

670
00:48:19,227 --> 00:48:20,436
he's one weary man.

671
00:48:23,856 --> 00:48:27,402
Well, I guess everyone
has their share of pain.

672
00:48:29,487 --> 00:48:31,906
Is that why you were drawn to him?

673
00:48:35,076 --> 00:48:37,036
You already knew?

674
00:48:37,120 --> 00:48:39,705
Hey, I can take a hint.

675
00:48:40,540 --> 00:48:42,583
That's why you're in charge of PM.

676
00:48:43,584 --> 00:48:45,878
Joo In-a definitely knows
where to place the right people.

677
00:48:49,132 --> 00:48:52,427
- Are we done here?
- I can also take a hint.

678
00:48:53,386 --> 00:48:55,388
What's going on
between Joo In-a and you?

679
00:48:57,640 --> 00:48:58,850
Is there something special?

680
00:49:04,188 --> 00:49:05,565
Where are you suddenly going?

681
00:49:05,648 --> 00:49:07,275
To find out what our relationship is.

682
00:49:16,451 --> 00:49:17,869
- Hey, Doo-gi.
- Yes?

683
00:49:17,952 --> 00:49:19,287
Where's Ms. Joo?

684
00:49:19,370 --> 00:49:21,205
She took the rest of the day off.
Can you believe it?

685
00:49:21,581 --> 00:49:23,166
She never takes a leave all year long

686
00:49:23,666 --> 00:49:24,917
so something must have happened.

687
00:49:25,585 --> 00:49:28,254
Can you also give me
the rest of the day off?

688
00:49:28,588 --> 00:49:29,672
What?

689
00:49:31,466 --> 00:49:33,217
You're suddenly taking
the rest of the day off?

690
00:49:34,093 --> 00:49:37,555
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

691
00:49:38,389 --> 00:49:39,640
Gosh.

692
00:50:05,625 --> 00:50:07,126
JOO IN-A

693
00:50:11,214 --> 00:50:14,342
Your call cannot be connected.
You will be redirected to voicemail.

694
00:50:20,515 --> 00:50:21,807
MS. JOO...

695
00:50:29,106 --> 00:50:30,858
- Hey, there.
- Hello.

696
00:50:31,108 --> 00:50:32,485
Your face scarred.

697
00:50:42,912 --> 00:50:43,913
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

698
00:50:43,996 --> 00:50:45,164
SHE IS INVOLVED IN AN INAPPROPRIATE
WORKPLACE RELATIONSHIP

699
00:50:50,253 --> 00:50:51,337
Could it be...

700
00:51:40,386 --> 00:51:41,387
Let's see.

701
00:52:01,198 --> 00:52:02,241
Joo In-a.

702
00:52:05,494 --> 00:52:06,662
Ms. Joo!

703
00:52:53,084 --> 00:52:54,627
You came, Ms. Joo.

704
00:52:55,461 --> 00:52:57,463
Don't even get me started, Jae-yeol.

705
00:52:57,546 --> 00:53:00,091
She kept insisting on not coming,
so I had to go to her place

706
00:53:00,174 --> 00:53:01,759
and force her to be here.

707
00:53:02,301 --> 00:53:03,344
Mr. Noh.

708
00:53:07,014 --> 00:53:10,559
I know. You were the guy
who gave the presentation.

709
00:53:10,643 --> 00:53:12,186
What brings you here?

710
00:53:13,604 --> 00:53:14,855
Well, the thing is...

711
00:53:17,566 --> 00:53:19,944
I had something urgent
to share with Ms. Joo.

712
00:53:26,283 --> 00:53:29,036
Goodness. What a passionate employee.

713
00:53:29,120 --> 00:53:31,997
You live up to your reputation.

714
00:53:32,081 --> 00:53:33,916
You can take your time
and talk to him, Ms. Joo.

715
00:53:33,999 --> 00:53:35,626
It's a lunch break anyway.

716
00:53:35,710 --> 00:53:37,294
Yes, he came all the way here

717
00:53:37,378 --> 00:53:39,422
so at least let him have
some fresh raw fish. Stay for lunch.

718
00:53:40,256 --> 00:53:41,757
- Yes, ma'am.
- Let's go.

719
00:54:00,151 --> 00:54:02,737
This must be an event
for the executives.

720
00:54:03,529 --> 00:54:05,030
It's held at a nice place.

721
00:54:05,614 --> 00:54:07,116
What's the urgent matter?

722
00:54:12,747 --> 00:54:14,039
Aren't you going to let me have fish?

723
00:54:14,707 --> 00:54:16,041
It's my favorite.

724
00:54:20,546 --> 00:54:23,632
This is so good.
It's so fresh and has a nice texture.

725
00:54:24,508 --> 00:54:26,385
You should have some, too.

726
00:54:28,387 --> 00:54:31,849
No, I should've made
a lettuce wrap for you.

727
00:54:31,932 --> 00:54:35,269
Now, tell me
what the urgent matter is.

728
00:54:36,729 --> 00:54:37,897
Well, you know.

729
00:54:38,981 --> 00:54:40,024
It's been resolved.

730
00:54:41,358 --> 00:54:42,359
In that while?

731
00:54:42,860 --> 00:54:46,197
You traveled this far for a matter
that could be resolved so quickly?

732
00:54:46,280 --> 00:54:48,199
Isn't it great
that it's been resolved quickly?

733
00:54:51,327 --> 00:54:53,829
Now, open up.

734
00:54:56,415 --> 00:54:57,666
You enjoy your food.

735
00:54:58,834 --> 00:55:00,294
Gosh. You're so cold.

736
00:55:10,221 --> 00:55:11,764
You seem to enjoy it a lot.

737
00:55:12,723 --> 00:55:15,267
Wait, did you really come here
to get raw fish?

738
00:55:15,476 --> 00:55:18,604
It's really good, so here.

739
00:55:19,063 --> 00:55:20,439
You should have some, too.

740
00:55:20,815 --> 00:55:22,274
Don't drink soju on an empty stomach.

741
00:55:22,650 --> 00:55:24,485
Or at least let me drink with you.
Here.

742
00:55:25,444 --> 00:55:26,612
Cheers.

743
00:55:36,372 --> 00:55:37,706
That's nice.

744
00:55:38,040 --> 00:55:40,209
So why did you suddenly take
the rest of the day off?

745
00:55:40,709 --> 00:55:42,711
People were surprised
that you did that.

746
00:55:43,087 --> 00:55:45,798
If I returned to the office
after the executive meeting

747
00:55:46,757 --> 00:55:48,133
people would spread rumors.

748
00:55:51,846 --> 00:55:54,640
If the urgency has been resolved,
let's finish eating and go.

749
00:55:54,723 --> 00:55:58,102
Let's take our time.
Mr. Jeon told us you could do that.

750
00:55:59,228 --> 00:56:00,312
I mean

751
00:56:00,980 --> 00:56:02,273
look at this.

752
00:56:02,606 --> 00:56:04,733
It's so nice to see the sea
for the first time in a while.

753
00:56:07,570 --> 00:56:08,737
It's like we're on a date.

754
00:56:16,662 --> 00:56:18,831
Mr. Noh, you're quite a simple guy.

755
00:56:27,423 --> 00:56:30,634
Yes, so keep it simple and finish
what you were going to say.

756
00:56:31,385 --> 00:56:32,928
- Say what?
- The answer

757
00:56:35,097 --> 00:56:36,348
you were about to give me.

758
00:56:36,849 --> 00:56:39,059
About your question, Mr. Noh...

759
00:56:40,477 --> 00:56:42,438
The real reason
why I keep pushing you away...

760
00:56:46,233 --> 00:56:47,276
I...

761
00:56:52,281 --> 00:56:53,449
Oh, that one.

762
00:57:04,585 --> 00:57:05,711
I...

763
00:57:21,936 --> 00:57:22,937
I forgot.

764
00:57:24,480 --> 00:57:27,149
I completely forgot what it was.
I've been so out of it.

765
00:57:28,192 --> 00:57:29,735
Let me try some raw fish.

766
00:57:32,655 --> 00:57:34,698
This place is delicious.

767
00:57:34,782 --> 00:57:36,617
Enjoy, Mr. Noh.
Do you want some soup too?

768
00:57:37,117 --> 00:57:39,870
Excuse me.
Can we have the spicy fish soup?

769
00:57:39,954 --> 00:57:41,372
And two bowls of rice!

770
00:57:43,374 --> 00:57:44,375
Cheers.

771
00:57:47,795 --> 00:57:49,171
Your glass is empty.

772
00:57:53,676 --> 00:57:54,677
Cheers.

773
00:58:07,022 --> 00:58:09,316
That happened at a coffee shop?

774
00:58:09,483 --> 00:58:11,068
I freaked out.

775
00:58:11,443 --> 00:58:13,278
He came over as if he'd punch me

776
00:58:13,362 --> 00:58:16,448
while everyone was watching
then suddenly knelt.

777
00:58:18,242 --> 00:58:20,411
I can imagine
what your face was like.

778
00:58:21,829 --> 00:58:22,955
Oh, my.

779
00:58:34,883 --> 00:58:35,968
Be careful.

780
00:58:39,680 --> 00:58:41,598
Hey. Don't be so cheeky.

781
00:58:45,102 --> 00:58:47,771
- Hands off.
- You tripped first, girl.

782
00:58:49,773 --> 00:58:50,816
"Girl"?

783
00:58:51,775 --> 00:58:53,402
Do you think you're my equal...

784
00:59:08,333 --> 00:59:09,543
Did you really forget

785
00:59:11,045 --> 00:59:12,588
what you were going to say to me?

786
00:59:15,591 --> 00:59:17,509
Why are you so dishonest?

787
00:59:25,434 --> 00:59:26,435
You.

788
00:59:27,061 --> 00:59:28,062
Why did you come here?

789
00:59:28,604 --> 00:59:29,772
What was the urgent matter?

790
00:59:35,027 --> 00:59:36,320
You lied, too.

791
00:59:38,155 --> 00:59:39,156
Wait, it's...

792
00:59:40,324 --> 00:59:41,825
It's embarrassing.

793
00:59:42,826 --> 00:59:45,329
Actually, I came running after you
because I lost my cool.

794
00:59:45,913 --> 00:59:47,664
I went to your place,
saw you get in Mr. Jeon's car

795
00:59:47,748 --> 00:59:49,500
and took it completely the wrong way.

796
00:59:50,209 --> 00:59:52,294
I lost it and raced all the way here.

797
00:59:53,253 --> 00:59:54,338
Isn't it hilarious?

798
00:59:54,421 --> 00:59:55,839
It's not like I'm your husband.

799
00:59:56,381 --> 00:59:57,466
Wait a second.

800
00:59:59,176 --> 01:00:00,677
Mr. Jeon and I?

801
01:00:05,516 --> 01:00:07,601
Was that why you called my name
in that scary tone?

802
01:00:08,352 --> 01:00:10,062
It sounded like
you wanted to punch him.

803
01:00:10,145 --> 01:00:11,688
Yes, exactly. I've gone crazy.

804
01:00:16,735 --> 01:00:18,403
I've lost a bit of my mind

805
01:00:19,696 --> 01:00:20,739
because of you.

806
01:00:26,995 --> 01:00:28,455
Stop feigning ignorance.

807
01:00:30,040 --> 01:00:31,375
You already know.

808
01:00:35,212 --> 01:00:36,338
You know that I like you.

809
01:00:41,802 --> 01:00:43,011
Hey, look.

810
01:00:45,013 --> 01:00:46,265
Where are you going?

811
01:00:47,057 --> 01:00:48,308
Wait! Come back here!

812
01:00:53,063 --> 01:00:54,690
You said you liked plushies, right?

813
01:01:03,157 --> 01:01:05,284
Now, let's get the plushie.

814
01:01:10,289 --> 01:01:11,874
Grab it. Grab it. Grab it.

815
01:01:26,513 --> 01:01:29,474
You're trying to get that, right?
Because of the gold bar.

816
01:01:29,558 --> 01:01:31,185
You're so materialistic.

817
01:01:32,227 --> 01:01:34,062
Move over. Let me try.

818
01:01:34,438 --> 01:01:36,607
You aren't
supposed to do this recklessly.

819
01:01:37,399 --> 01:01:38,692
You need good skills.

820
01:02:01,924 --> 01:02:03,133
Look.

821
01:02:04,176 --> 01:02:06,595
Right here, you're going to drop...

822
01:02:11,767 --> 01:02:12,809
Down.

823
01:02:14,728 --> 01:02:16,104
You can't win that.

824
01:02:16,813 --> 01:02:18,106
I can tell that this crane machine

825
01:02:18,190 --> 01:02:21,151
holds the claws tightly
only for about three seconds.

826
01:02:21,818 --> 01:02:23,654
And that bear has
metal lumps in its hands

827
01:02:23,737 --> 01:02:24,988
which makes it too heavy to lift.

828
01:02:26,949 --> 01:02:28,909
It doesn't matter
if you try 1,000 or 10,000 times.

829
01:02:29,451 --> 01:02:30,494
You can't win.

830
01:02:31,828 --> 01:02:35,290
It's not that you're unlucky
or not talented enough.

831
01:02:36,500 --> 01:02:38,543
It's just programmed that way.

832
01:02:39,586 --> 01:02:40,796
Something that can't work

833
01:02:42,464 --> 01:02:44,091
can never work even if you're reborn.

834
01:02:51,598 --> 01:02:52,933
That's my answer.

835
01:02:54,685 --> 01:02:55,852
I can't...

836
01:03:00,190 --> 01:03:01,358
be with you.

837
01:03:02,067 --> 01:03:03,610
That's just how I'm set.

838
01:03:05,988 --> 01:03:08,490
First, you're under my authority.

839
01:03:09,658 --> 01:03:11,785
That already is something
I'm not willing to risk.

840
01:03:15,580 --> 01:03:16,748
Also, I believe

841
01:03:18,333 --> 01:03:20,544
you're getting
your feelings confused.

842
01:03:21,545 --> 01:03:23,547
It's probably curiosity or pity.

843
01:03:24,464 --> 01:03:25,632
Think about it.

844
01:03:26,049 --> 01:03:28,385
You've received too much information
about me in a short while.

845
01:03:28,969 --> 01:03:31,471
You've seen me naked,
and you know about my family.

846
01:03:32,306 --> 01:03:33,682
You kept seeing me like this

847
01:03:34,349 --> 01:03:38,186
and began to think,
"She's a poor, lonely woman."

848
01:03:39,688 --> 01:03:40,897
That's probably it.

849
01:03:41,732 --> 01:03:43,817
Don't define how I feel about you.

850
01:03:44,484 --> 01:03:46,028
Well, that was how it began.

851
01:03:48,113 --> 01:03:49,323
Can you deny that?

852
01:03:54,453 --> 01:03:55,454
Is that bad?

853
01:03:56,330 --> 01:03:57,956
Be it pity or curiosity

854
01:03:58,457 --> 01:04:00,083
the feeling of affection
is all the same.

855
01:04:01,001 --> 01:04:03,503
Can you label feelings
into one, pity, and two, love

856
01:04:03,587 --> 01:04:06,298
as if they were elements
on the periodic table?

857
01:04:06,965 --> 01:04:08,800
Wanting to hold the other person,
missing them

858
01:04:08,884 --> 01:04:11,094
feeling bad for them, pitying them

859
01:04:11,178 --> 01:04:13,764
getting curious, and feeling jealous.

860
01:04:17,059 --> 01:04:18,769
Aren't those
all part of liking someone?

861
01:04:27,069 --> 01:04:28,945
I don't like feelings
that stem from pity.

862
01:04:30,155 --> 01:04:32,115
There's nothing more pathetic

863
01:04:33,700 --> 01:04:34,951
and stickier than that.

864
01:04:36,036 --> 01:04:38,413
I can't help you
even if you can't accept that.

865
01:04:40,165 --> 01:04:41,500
Something that can't work

866
01:04:43,710 --> 01:04:44,878
simply can't work.

867
01:05:09,861 --> 01:05:13,031
So you two have never fought?

868
01:05:13,115 --> 01:05:14,282
I'm telling you.

869
01:05:14,699 --> 01:05:16,743
Actually, I've always been cheeky

870
01:05:17,244 --> 01:05:18,995
but he always let me win.

871
01:05:19,079 --> 01:05:20,455
I'm glad to hear that you know.

872
01:05:23,750 --> 01:05:28,004
Doesn't that mean
you adored the managing director?

873
01:05:28,088 --> 01:05:29,506
I still find him adorable.

874
01:05:30,924 --> 01:05:34,052
Oh, my. He must adore you a lot.

875
01:05:34,553 --> 01:05:36,847
Are you reminded of the old days?

876
01:05:36,930 --> 01:05:38,390
Yes, of course, he does.

877
01:05:39,182 --> 01:05:40,267
Are you listening to me?

878
01:05:41,226 --> 01:05:45,230
Does Jae-yeol choose not to talk
or is he unable to talk?

879
01:05:52,904 --> 01:05:54,281
Come on.

880
01:06:05,459 --> 01:06:06,960
Darn it.

881
01:06:22,476 --> 01:06:25,562
Something that can't work
can never work even if you're reborn.

882
01:06:26,521 --> 01:06:27,731
That's my answer.

883
01:06:48,001 --> 01:06:49,753
I apologize
for what happened earlier.

884
01:06:54,049 --> 01:06:56,134
Oh, about your wife slapping me?

885
01:06:56,927 --> 01:06:58,637
All I expect
is a lot of salary in return.

886
01:07:03,892 --> 01:07:04,893
Are you all right?

887
01:07:06,019 --> 01:07:07,312
It's not a big deal.

888
01:07:07,938 --> 01:07:10,774
I can take my blows,
so I'm all right.

889
01:07:19,407 --> 01:07:21,409
I thought you were looking at the sea

890
01:07:23,245 --> 01:07:24,788
but you were
looking into the darkness.

891
01:07:28,833 --> 01:07:31,169
This expensive ocean view hotel
is useless at night.

892
01:07:31,878 --> 01:07:34,506
You can't tell where the sea ends
and where the sky begins.

893
01:07:35,757 --> 01:07:36,967
It's only dark.

894
01:07:38,218 --> 01:07:39,928
But you can still feel it.

895
01:07:41,555 --> 01:07:43,306
The sea breeze blows

896
01:07:44,182 --> 01:07:45,767
and you can hear the waves.

897
01:07:57,404 --> 01:07:59,739
Please excuse me. Get a good rest.

898
01:08:00,532 --> 01:08:01,575
In-a.

899
01:08:09,916 --> 01:08:11,126
Let go.

900
01:08:12,794 --> 01:08:13,878
Let go.

901
01:08:15,839 --> 01:08:17,048
Let go of me.

902
01:08:17,132 --> 01:08:19,092
One moment. In-a, wait.

903
01:08:19,175 --> 01:08:20,885
She wants you to let go.

904
01:08:30,520 --> 01:08:31,521
Let go of her.

905
01:08:41,072 --> 01:08:42,115
See?

906
01:08:44,200 --> 01:08:45,452
Something that can't work

907
01:08:46,703 --> 01:08:47,912
still can work.

908
01:09:10,060 --> 01:09:12,937
FILING FOR LOVE

909
01:09:13,605 --> 01:09:16,149
GUEST APPEARANCE BY OH HYE-WON

910
01:09:41,299 --> 01:09:43,218
Actually, we go way back.

911
01:09:43,301 --> 01:09:44,969
- It's all in the past.
- I know the vice president

912
01:09:45,053 --> 01:09:47,222
has feelings for Ms. Joo In-a.

913
01:09:47,305 --> 01:09:50,016
Is this the vice president's
one-sided feeling?

914
01:09:50,642 --> 01:09:53,061
Or is there something left
between you two?

915
01:09:53,144 --> 01:09:55,105
Do you have anyone like that?

916
01:09:55,188 --> 01:09:57,357
Someone who always takes your side
no matter what happens.

917
01:09:57,440 --> 01:09:59,275
You have a clinical condition
of acting tough.

918
01:09:59,359 --> 01:10:01,653
Who cares if you act a little crazy?

919
01:10:01,986 --> 01:10:03,947
I don't care how long it takes.

920
01:10:04,447 --> 01:10:06,241
Take a good look at your feelings.

921
01:10:07,242 --> 01:10:08,535
I'll wait.

922
01:10:22,382 --> 01:10:24,384
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim
